A song from the album has even made it to the radio hit - the recently broadcasting from early to late pop music mr2 Petőfi has successively set the earworm to the listeners with the number "Wings of Love", which was recorded with the participation of six local singers ("Underground Divas").
All right so (?).
The hvg.hu asked Balázs Zságer.
hvg.hu: This new hit raises the question: To what extent is your music reserved for a certain layer?
Balázs Zságer: The term "layer music" doesn't exactly mean much to me.
In my opinion, there are two boxes in pop music, not mainstream and underground, or alternative and pop, but commercial and honest.
Even the so-called alternative or underground music can be shallow and meaningless, but they can also only be produced for the sale, which makes them commercial music.
A good pop number can also come from an honest motif.
The listener’s willingness to record also works according to this principle, independently of languages and national borders.
hvg.hu: Do you see a difference in the openness of the Hungarian and foreign audiences to your music?
B. Zs.: Abroad, especially west of us, pop music has a greater tradition.
Not only teenagers or twens go to concerts, but also the older audience.
They follow the trends in pop music that happen around them much more attentively because they also consider them a part of contemporary culture.
hvg.hu: What role does the audience play in your work?
Is it important who, where, how many people hear your music?
B. Zs.: Of course, it is a good feeling to see that more and more come to our concerts.
We never composed for the market.
In our case, the music does not arise in order to serve a purpose, but for a specific reason.
The role of the audience is mostly noticeable at the concerts, where there is already a mutual interaction, but these in turn only exist in the intangible changes of the moment.
Nevertheless, I noticed one thing: If you want to please everyone, you are no longer interesting.
hvg.hu: How far would you like to follow the example of Yonderboi?
He is on the road as a soloist and has built his career more in the West.
B. Zs.: We don’t really go our way, not to mention that you always try to interpret this into our music.
We see ourselves more as a team player who trust in the musical presence of the other and let them unfold.
Initially, of course, comparisons of our work with that of Yonderboi were inevitable, as several of us come from his band and took a different path.
hvg.hu: In the charts of mr2 Petőfi, "Wings of Love" comes first.
Many have only heard the name Zagar in connection with this number.
Was the opening deliberately staged with a somewhat more popular style towards a wider audience?
B. Zs.: We had no plans to write a hit, which should then be a draught horse for the album.
This song is about more.
It was intended as the finale of the album, with which we wanted to dissolve the sound orgy and the slightly more difficult topics.
hvg.hu: How did you choose the six singers?
Why them, what was the guiding principle?
B. Zs.: The basic idea was to make a gospel-like choir.
Then came the idea to put together the choir of gifted soloists from the local music scene.
This is how the six-member choir was created - that's how Sena, Edina Kutzora, Judie Jay, Bori Péterfy, Enikő Hodosi [Neo], Juci Németh - were born, which we then christened "Underground Divas" later.
hvg.hu: Did you want to have the song the same way, or did the girls help shape it?
B. Zs.: The number had been in the instrumental version for a long time, but when the material for the album was finished, we thought that this number still "needs something."
The chord sequence has formally demanded a singing voice.
I sang the tune the same night, later they learned the girls.
It all came practically straight away and terrifyingly spontaneous.
I can remember, I was quite electrified at the time, but it also required the "Divas".
With my voice alone, the song would never have become so powerful.
hvg.hu: Both on the record and at the concert, however, one had the impression that the girls were in the background.
There is no solo part (apart from the short solo of Judy Jay), they don't have a role of their own, sing together and are no louder than the music, so their singing is not only accompanied by the music.
They were also on the stage in the back.
Is it intentional?
B.Zs.: That they stood in the back was like that because of purely technical problems.
However, we deliberately did not want to give them solo roles.
The number is also about forgetting your ego a little, forgetting who came from where and where is going, we simply allow these certain wings to lift us up the wings of love.
I would like others to feel this euphoric state that we felt when the song was created.
hvg.hu: Which was the most elaborate song?
B. Zs.: In the musical work actually none at all, there have been more difficult tasks in the mixing.
For example, on "Dorian Gray's Dilemma", in which I play on a concert piano, or on "Rock'n'Roll Goes To The Girls", where the groove did not want to work for a long time, but gradually everything has joined together, as with a puzzle.
hvg.hu: Which is your favorite number from the new album?
B. Zs.: This changes with the concerts constantly and also now, where I have "let go" of the album.
Currently it's "Prophet Is A Fool," "Escape From The Earth" and the number "Never The Same."
