But I don't expect such a change," he noted.
Debts are growing
The national debt stems from the debts of the state government and comes mainly from the accumulation of deficits in the state budget.
The government debt is financed by Treasury notes, state bonds, direct bonds or, for example, by bonds issued by the European Investment Bank.
Domestic debt has now risen to 719.4 billion kronor this year.
The state's foreign debt, meanwhile, rose by 1.7 billion crowns to 123.3 billion.
The so-called marketable sovereign debt reached 803.3 billion crowns at the end of September, falling by 13.7 billion since June.
The average maturity of the national debt rose to 6.5 years.
"Total debt rose 13 percent over the year from the first to the third quarter, which is really a lot given how well the economy is doing.
