It's bad that the debt is rising, but on the other hand this shows that you can do something even before the pension reform comes," Pikora commented on the data.
Better than expected
The financing strategy and the handling of the national debt for 2007 shows that the government had planned for this year to take up 159.2 billion crowns.
At the beginning of December, however, thanks to the better development of the state budget policy, the ministry reduced the plan to 152.8 billion crowns.
This amount stems mainly from the state budget deficit, which this year will obviously reach 76 billion crowns instead of the estimated 91.3 billion.
Furthermore, it is a maximum budgeted fund for the consolidation agency in the amount of 13.3 billion kronor, a ten billion reserve to pay the pensions, the financing of government bonds for 43 billion and instalments for the bonds at the European Investment Bank of 1.8 billion.
