The tool he used, a mini hockey racket, wrapped with insulator to prevent an electric shock on the solar panels that generate several hundred volts, the astronauts had devised and "crafted" on board the station.
When the action was finished, Scott Parazynski waited until the collector was fully unfolded before counting his tools and returning to the station.
