Which insurance is best for me?
The motor vehicle insurance, which covers a possible claim caused by the driver, includes a high cost, the amount of which in turn depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of preparation of the driver's license, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, you have to be clear about what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and a policyholder.
This agreement is stipulated in writing by means of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to submit the corresponding severance payment amount in the event of a claim.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance company composed by several factors, including Age, gender, time of preparation of the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that higher contribution payments are also due in the event of a higher risk of accidents.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women have to make fewer contributions, because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of the companies, these tend to fewer accidents like single people.
The benefit given to the vehicle impairs the frequency of driving and thus also the likelihood of an accident.
The more often the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, insurance companies must consider a whole range of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that most closely meets his personal needs.
At this point, we now list the most important points that should be considered when choosing an insurance company in order to be able to make not only a performance-oriented but also a price-oriented choice.
The under-25s encounter numerous obstacles when choosing a low-priced insurance company, such as the low driving practice and the young driver's license.
Even if it were best for an ideal insurance cover to take out full comprehensive insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full comprehensive case with a deductible, so that the services of a fully comprehensive insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract includes that the customer has to pay a part of the amount incurred by the damage himself.
The amount is determined before the conclusion of the contract and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium. This is higher the less the amount to be paid," explains Luis Noguera, Spain's main representative at First Europa, an online insurance agency.
Another option is the extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accidental damage, but not against the damage to the own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's a piece of advice.
If you are under the age of 25, it is up to your hand to reduce insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction of the basic tariff at the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment includes an increase in said tariff.
The amount of credits and penalties depend on society and its income.
If the company has a high-yielding year behind it, it can allow itself to increase the bonus payments," explains Noguera.
Once the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to sign a contract. The reason for this is the fact that with increasing driving experience, the accident rate decreases.
Thus, it makes the most sense to opt for a full comprehensive insurance with a deductible.
“Normally, the young people can’t benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving,” explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice, after the “fear of the beginner” has been abandoned.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to take out full comprehensive insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the corresponding person also allows it.
On the part of the insurers, married couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly, their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, a full comprehensive insurance with excess (with an amount around 300 euros) would be the best option. In the event that a high credit has been received, an extended insurance is recommended, which only starts for the third year of the vehicle.
“They drive more relaxed overall and have greater purchasing power, which allows them to make a higher contribution payment,” notes Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a full comprehensive insurance with a deductible (with an amount of around 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which only starts with a sufficiently high credit.
Ultimately, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accidental damage, but also because it entails high costs, which require a thorough selection to be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
